definitions.definition: Of, or pertaining to, conditions unique to the descendant species of a clade , and not found in earlier ancestral species.
Possessing features believed to be more advanced or improved than those other organisms.

examples: The French language is derived from Latin.

main_definition: ( systematics ) Of, or pertaining to, conditions unique to the descendant species of a clade , and not found in earlier ancestral species.
secondary_definitions: ( comparable , archaic , taxonomy ) Possessing features believed to be more advanced or improved than those other organisms.
